title: Armed Man Shot Dead After Entering Trump‚Äôs Mar-A-Lago Florida Resort | 10 News
description: An armed man has been shot dead after entering the secure perimeter of US President Donald Trump's Mar-a-Lago residence in Florida on Sunday.  The 21-year-old man was carrying a shotgun, and a fuel can at the resort's north gate around 1:30am, before two US Secret Service agents and a deputy confronted the man and ordered him to drop the two items.  The suspect has been named as Austin T Martin, whose family in North Carolina had reported him missing in the early hours of Sunday morning.  Investigations are continuing. title: Cartel Boss 'El Mencho' Killed By Mexican Forces, Sparking Violent Riots | 10 News
description: A wave of violence has swept through half a dozen Mexican states with torched cars and gunmen blocking multiple highways after the killing of cartel kingpin ‚ÄòEl Mencho‚Äô.  The former police-officer turned drug lord was killed in an operation led by the Mexican military ending in a shootout that left four gang members dead, and three officers injured.  Hundreds have been trapped in the city of Puerto Vallarta, with tourists being told to "shelter in place" as airlines cancel flights in and out of the city.  The Mexican President says activities had been "normal" for most of the country urging residents to stay calm.
